name: Arctic Circle
overview: During a routine search of an old cabin in the remote and wintery back country, Finnish policewoman, Nina Kautsalo, discovers two dead prostitutes, with a third still fighting for her life. The ensuing investigation takes a surprise twist when an extremely rare and deadly virus is discovered in the surviving woman’s bloodwork. When the Finnish Bureau of Investigation takes over the case, German virologist, Thomas Lorenz is called in to assist in identifying and containing the virus.  Set within the endless white expanse of the arctic circle, Nina and Thomas must rely on each other to have any hope of saving the ones they love. But what takes precedence? A deadly virus or an active serial killer?

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Nina Kautsalo has moved to Rovaniemi in northern Finland, where her daughter has started special school and her mother is undergoing cancer treatment. Nina joins a new Finnish-Russian police team and is partnered with the mysterious Viktor. A new investigation leads them to Murmansk on the trail of a mysterious hunting club. The case also involves an unsolved old murder whose prime suspect has disappeared.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: Nina Kautsalo returns to Ivalo, where she starts investigating the murder of a local pharmacist as chief of police. Meanwhile, an attempt is made to hijack a top-secret test car. Soon the murder investigation led by Nina also points in the direction of the international car business.

episodes.name: Cellar
episodes.overview: Finnish police Nina Kautsalo makes a horrific discovery in the basement of wilderness cabin. Soon the find brings German virologist, Thomas Lorenz, to work on the case.

episodes.name: Tracks In The Snow
episodes.overview: National Bureau of Investigation joins the investigation and Nina is forced off the case. Tracks in the snow give her a new lead, however.

episodes.name: Storm Rises
episodes.overview: Raunola, the man suspected for the murders is leaving the investigators confused. The virus investigation takes a bad turn, and Nina and Thomas find each other in surprising place.

episodes.name: An Eye for an Eye
episodes.overview: Both crime and virus investigations are progressing slowly. Work and personal life are starting to mix for both Nina and Thomas.

episodes.name: God's Peace
episodes.overview: Virus investigation becomes even more topical. Police track down the fourth victim.

episodes.name: First Victim
episodes.overview: Nina gets a chance to interrogate the fourth woman. Esko gets into trouble with the police. The first victim wakes up from coma.

episodes.name: Predator
episodes.overview: Nina and Thomas are in danger when Raunola returns to Ivalo. Marita gets bad news in quarantine.

episodes.name: Carriers
episodes.overview: Nina and Thomas get new information from a surprising source. Thomas has to fight for his daughter's custody. Virus infection takes a frightening turn.

episodes.name: Murmansk
episodes.overview: Nina and Thomas participate in an illegal expedition to Murmansk. Venla is fighting for her life.

episodes.name: Venla
episodes.overview: Nina and Thomas return to Finland. Venla gets help from unexpected source. Nina will have to step into the darkness once more.

episodes.name: Return
episodes.overview: Nina Kautsalo has returned to Ivalo as she is set to become the new Chief of Police. When a local pharmacist is found murdered, Nina is assigned to investigate the case as her last assignment with her old partner Aikio. Meanwhile, an American car manufacturer's test car is attempted to be hijacked.
